/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
// Problems and Solutions - Uploading sketch error
///////////////////////////////////////////////////
// Connection Problem.
// .. The microcontroller is not detected by Mac OS X
// .. The microcontroller does not run. When starting, a Led lights up and down and finished.
//////////////////////////////////////
// Device under ports missing: /dev/cu.wchusbserial1420
// + https://github.com/esp8266/Arduino/issues/732
// + https://arduino.stackexchange.com/questions/34775/arduino-nano-not-visible-in-serial-ports-mac-os
// + http://yucelkilic.com/clone-arduino-mega-and-usb-connection-issue-in-mac-os-x-sierra/?i=1
// + http://www.dhiravat.com/install-ch340g-usb-driver-on-macos-sierra/
// + https://blog.sengotta.net/signed-mac-os-driver-for-winchiphead-ch340-serial-bridge/
// + http://www.mblock.cc/docs/run-makeblock-ch340-ch341-on-mac-os-sierra/
//////////////////////////////
// 1. Remove the old driver by issuing one of the following commands (depending on your installation):
// sudo rm -rf /System/Library/Extensions/usb.kext
// sudo rm -rf /Library/Extensions/usbserial.kext
// 2. Restart your Mac.
// 3. Install the driver by the following commands:
//  $ brew tap mengbo/ch340g-ch34g-ch34x-mac-os-x-driver https://github.com/mengbo/ch340g-ch34g-ch34x-mac-os-x-driver
//  $ brew cask install wch-ch34x-usb-serial-driver
//////////////////////////////////
// Uninstall Packages on Mac OS X
// + https://wincent.com/wiki/Uninstalling_packages_(.pkg_files)_on_Mac_OS_X
